<P>
The Michael Nunn-Marlon Starling bout for the International Boxing Federation 
middleweight championship, postponed after Nunn suffered a back injury, has 
been rescheduled for April 14. 
</P>
<P>
The fight was originally scheduled for last Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
It will be the second boxing event at The Mirage Resort, the first in the 
hotel's 4,600-seat arena. 
</P>
<P>
Nunn, 34-0 with 23 knockouts, will defend his title. Starling, 45-5-1 with 27 
knockouts, is the World Boxing Council welterweight champion. 
</P>
